          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "QMPH",
                  "ARAD"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Positron annihilation in flight.",
                "Photon energy resolution is typical for livermore",
                " facility experiments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 5.55-mole helium gas sample was contained at a",
                " pressure of 30.61 mpa (about 300 atm)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An efficient paraffin-and-BF3-tube neutron 4pi",
                " detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "After the recorded neutron events were corrected for",
                " pileup in the detector, the neutron backgrounds",
                " (annihilation target removed) were substracted for",
                " both the positron and electron measurements.",
                "Because the energy spectrum of the annihilation-plus-",
                " Bremsstrahlung radiation differs from that of purely",
                " Bremsstrahlung photons, a measured correction was",
                " applied to the ion-chamber (beam monitor) response to",
                " normalize the electron data to the positron data.",
                "The normalized electron data then were substracted from",
                " the positron data, leaving the neutron counts which",
                " result only from the annihilation radiation.",
                "The measured sample-blank data, normalized to equal",
                " photon flux, were substracted from the target data to",
                " give the net target results.",
                "After a small correction for the neutron multiplicity",
                " in each ring, the data were corrected for the energy-",
                " dependent efficiency of the neutron detector using the",
                " ring-ratio result for each energy.",
                "The data were converted to photoneutron cross sections",
                " by applying the measured ion-chamber response per",
                " photon, the known number of target nuclei in the beam",
                " and a small correction for the photon attenuation in",
                " the sample.",
                "A multiplicity analysis of the number of neutrons",
                " recordered in each beam burst allows the (gamma,n) and",
                " (gamma,2n) yields to be extracted simultaneously and",
                " independently."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors only."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " There are several possible sources of",
                " systematic errors:",
                " - uncertainty in the photon flux calibration: no",
                "   greater than 5% at 22 MeV, but rises to about 10%",
                "   at 45 MeV.",
                " - uncertainty in the neutron-detector efficiency",
                "   >3% for neutrons of 2 MeV (E(gamma) about 23 MeV),",
                "   rising to about 5% for E(n) = 14 MeV, and, perhaps,",
                "   to 8% for E(n) = 18 MeV (E(gamma) about 45 MeV).",
                " - uncertaintiy arising from the Bremsstrahlung yield",
                "   substraction: never more than 2% of the yield, WHIC",
                "   translates into about 10% of the cross section at",
                "   35 MeV.",
                " - uncertainty arising from the sample-blank yield:",
                "   could be as much as 15% above 42 MeV.",
                "The data points at 25.3, 26.3 MeV, and, perhaps, at",
                " 28.3 MeV, have systematic uncertainties as large as",
                " 15%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Results agree with earlier monoenergetic-photon and",
                " certain photoneutron time-of-flight (liquid-sample)",
                " results at the lower energies, and consequently",
                " disagree with the results of other experiments at",
                " these energies. At the higher energies, however, the",
                " present results are essentially in agreement with all",
                " previous results."
              ]
            }
          ],
